@startuml component-keybindings-inprogress
'' Current custom-keybinding architecture.
!include _vv-theme.iuml

title Custom keybindings — command registry, palette, resolver, editor, persistence

rectangle "DOM keydown" as KD #2D9574
rectangle "vinary.input.keys\nKeyboardEvent -> canonical chord" as KEYS #2D9574
rectangle "vinary.input.resolver\nmodal/chord state machine" as RES #2D9574
rectangle "vinary.input.keymap\nactive keymap atom" as KM #A45BAD
rectangle "resources/keymaps/*.edn\nStandard / Vim / Emacs" as PRESETS #A45BAD
rectangle "vinary.input.keymaps-registry\napp-db registry helpers" as REG #7590DB
rectangle "vinary.app.commands\ncommand registry" as CMD #4F97D7
rectangle "vinary.ui.palette\ncommand/file palette" as PAL #2D9574
rectangle "vinary.ui.keybindings-editor\nvisual editor + undo/redo" as EDIT #2D9574
rectangle "vinary.main.config\nkeybindings.edn watch/save" as CONFIG #3A5BA0
database "~/.config/vinary-viewer/keybindings.edn" as EDN #9F8766
rectangle "re-frame dispatch/effects" as RF #4F97D7

PRESETS --> KM : compile-time defaults
CONFIG --> EDN : read/write/watch
CONFIG --> REG : vv:keymap
EDIT --> REG : edit custom sets
PAL --> CMD : choose command
KD --> KEYS
KEYS --> RES
RES --> KM : read modes/trie
RES --> CMD : resolved command id
REG --> KM : install active set
CMD --> RF : dispatch command

note bottom
  The system is available now: built-in sets, custom sets, persisted EDN,
  modal/chord resolver, command palette, visual editor, and live installation
  of the active keymap.
end note

legend right
  |= color |= concept |
  | <#2D9574> | renderer UI/input |
  | <#7590DB> | app-db registry state |
  | <#A45BAD> | keymap data |
  | <#4F97D7> | re-frame command/effect layer |
  | <#3A5BA0> | main process config service |
  | <#9F8766> | user config file |
endlegend
@enduml
